Compare Groups with PARENTGROUPVAL() and PREVGROUPVAL()
Write row level formulas to evaluate each record in a report. 
Use PARENTGROUPVAL to calculate values relative to a parent grouping, and PREVGROUPVAL to calculate values relative to a peer grouping.
Available in: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs) and Lightning Experience
Available in: Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions
Enhanced Folder Sharing required.

Required User Permissions:
To create, edit, and delete formulas in private reports: Enhanced Folder Sharing
Create and Customize Reports

To create, edit, and delete formulas in public and private reports: Enhanced Folder Sharing
title: Calculating Values Relative to Parent or Peer Group in Salesforce Reports
